<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<?xml-model href="https://www.tei-c.org/release/xml/tei/custom/schema/relaxng/tei_odds.rng" type="application/xml" schematypens="http://relaxng.org/ns/structure/1.0"?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:eg="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
  <teiHeader>
    <fileDesc>
      <titleStmt>
        <title>TEI Simler: A focused TEI customization for the Simler Digital Scholarly Edition</title>
        <author>Simler Project Team</author>
      </titleStmt>
      <publicationStmt>
        <p>Distributed as part of the Simler Oxygen Author Framework.</p>
      </publicationStmt>
      <sourceDesc>
        <p>This ODD was created from scratch as a slim, project-focused replacement for the
          adapted <ref target="https://www.deutschestextarchiv.de/doku/basisformat/">DTA-Basisformat
          (DTABf)</ref> customization (<ident>basisformat_all_customized.odd</ident>). Its scope is
          derived primarily from the encoding of Simler's
          <hi rend="italic">Teutsche Gedichte</hi>; it selects only the elements, attributes and
          values that edition actually uses, and follows the documentation conventions of the TEI
          <ref target="https://github.com/TEIC/TEI/blob/dev/P5/Exemplars/tei_simplePrint.odd"
            >Simple Print (tei_simplePrint)</ref> exemplar — in particular, the appearance of the
          source is recorded with <gi>rendition</gi> declarations in <gi>tagsDecl</gi> referenced
          from the global <att>rendition</att> attribute.</p>
      </sourceDesc>
    </fileDesc>
    <encodingDesc>
      <projectDesc>
        <p>TEI Simler is a TEI P5 customization for the digital scholarly edition of the collected
          poems of the Zurich poet Johann Wilhelm Simler (1605–1672). Several editions of the
          <hi rend="italic">Teutsche Gedichte</hi> are transcribed (A 1648, B 1653, C 1663, D 1688
          and minor pieces); this schema is intended to
          serve the whole corpus. The transcription is a line- and page-faithful diplomatic rendering
          of early-modern printed books set mainly in Fraktur (blackletter) type.</p>
      </projectDesc>
      <editorialDecl>
        <p>The transcription preserves the physical layout of the printed source: every printed line
          <emph>end</emph> is marked with <gi>lb</gi> (following the DTABf convention — the line break
          is set after the outermost closing element), every page with <gi>pb</gi>, and hyphenation
          across a line is encoded with <gi>lb</gi> <att>break</att>=<val>no</val> (the hyphen being
          retained). Verse is encoded with <gi>lg</gi> and
          <gi>l</gi>; front matter (title pages, dedications, frontispieces) with <gi>front</gi>,
          <gi>titlePage</gi> and typed <gi>div</gi>. The appearance of the source (Antiqua within
          Fraktur, bold, centring, indentation, initials, letter-spacing, small capitals, super-
          script, larger/smaller type) is recorded on <att>rendition</att> using the pointer tokens
          declared in <gi>tagsDecl</gi>.</p>
        <p>Obvious printing errors are corrected with <gi>choice</gi> (<gi>sic</gi>/<gi>corr</gi>);
          unreadable passages with <gi>unclear</gi>; editorially supplied text with <gi>supplied</gi>.
          Named entities are tagged with <gi>rs</gi> carrying <att>type</att> and a typed
          <att>key</att>. Editorial comments are anchored with <gi>anchor</gi> pairs and held in
          <gi>note</gi>.</p>
        <p>The source files are a work in progress; content models and value lists are kept
          deliberately permissive (suggested rather than closed value lists) so that minor encoding
          variation does not invalidate a document.</p>
      </editorialDecl>
      <tagsDecl>
        <!-- Source appearance, declared once and pointed to from @rendition (simplePrint style).
             The CSS records how the passage looks in the SOURCE, not any intended output. -->
        <rendition xml:id="aq" scheme="css">font-family: serif;</rendition><!-- Antiqua within Fraktur -->
        <rendition xml:id="b" scheme="css">font-weight: bold;</rendition>
        <rendition xml:id="i" scheme="css">font-style: italic;</rendition>
        <rendition xml:id="c" scheme="css">text-align: center;</rendition>
        <rendition xml:id="right" scheme="css">text-align: right;</rendition>
        <rendition xml:id="g" scheme="css">letter-spacing: 0.125em;</rendition><!-- gesperrt -->
        <rendition xml:id="k" scheme="css">font-variant: small-caps;</rendition><!-- Kapitälchen -->
        <rendition xml:id="in" scheme="css">font-size: 2em; line-height: 1;</rendition><!-- Initiale -->
        <rendition xml:id="sup" scheme="css">vertical-align: super; font-size: smaller;</rendition>
        <rendition xml:id="larger" scheme="css">font-size: larger;</rendition>
        <rendition xml:id="smaller" scheme="css">font-size: smaller;</rendition>
        <rendition xml:id="et" scheme="css">text-indent: 2em;</rendition>
        <rendition xml:id="et2" scheme="css">text-indent: 4em;</rendition>
        <rendition xml:id="et3" scheme="css">text-indent: 6em;</rendition>
        <rendition xml:id="hr" scheme="css">display: block; border-top: 1px solid; width: 30%; margin: 0.5em auto;</rendition>
        <!-- Page-layout renditions for the interleaved two-column / acrostic poems.
             The layout *is* the rendition: an <lg rendition="#twocol"> becomes a 2-column CSS grid
             whose row-major auto-flow reproduces the line-1-left / line-1-right
             reading order; an <l rendition="#acrostic"> becomes a 3-cell mini-grid
             pinning the marginal initial/final letters into aligned name columns. -->
        <rendition xml:id="twocol" scheme="css">display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; column-gap: 2.5em; align-items: baseline;</rendition>
        <rendition xml:id="acrostic" scheme="css">display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1.4em 1fr 1.4em; column-gap: 0.15em; align-items: baseline;</rendition>
        <rendition xml:id="acroInit" scheme="css">grid-column: 1; text-align: left;</rendition>
        <rendition xml:id="acroFin" scheme="css">grid-column: 3; text-align: right;</rendition>
      </tagsDecl>
    </encodingDesc>
  </teiHeader>
  <text>
    <body>
      <head>TEI Simler: A focused TEI customization for the Simler Digital Scholarly Edition</head>

      <p>This document defines TEI Simler, a slim customization of the
        <ref target="https://tei-c.org/guidelines/">TEI Guidelines</ref> for the digital scholarly
        edition of Johann Wilhelm Simler's <hi rend="italic">Teutsche Gedichte</hi>. It reproduces the
        validation behaviour of the project's previous, much larger DTABf-derived schema for the
        existing source files, while excluding the many DTABf modules, elements and attributes that
        the project does not use (drama, manuscript description, tables, apparatus, etc.).</p>

      <p>Each source document is a printed edition encoded within a <gi>TEI</gi> element holding a
        <gi>teiHeader</gi> and one <gi>text</gi>. The <gi>text</gi> may open with <gi>front</gi>
        matter (title page, dedication, frontispiece) and continues with a <gi>body</gi> containing a
        hierarchy of <gi>div</gi> elements (book → poem) whose verse is encoded with <gi>lg</gi> and
        <gi>l</gi>.</p>

      <schemaSpec ident="tei_simler" start="TEI" prefix="tei_" targetLang="de" docLang="en">

        <!-- ===================================================================
             PROCESSING MODEL
             Each <model> below maps a Simler element to a PM behaviour so the
             build-time spine (odd-to-unified -> render-unified) renders the
             edition straight from this ODD. Source typography (italic, bold,
             centring, indentation, initials) is deliberately NOT repeated here:
             it stays in <tagsDecl> and is applied through the @rendition
             pointers, which odd-to-static compiles into .r-* CSS rules.
             NB: for readability the <model> is written first inside each
             <elementSpec>; a strict ODD sequence places it after <attList>.
             =================================================================== -->

        <!-- ===================================================================
             MODULES — only those the Simler edition uses
             =================================================================== -->
        <moduleRef key="header" include="teiHeader fileDesc titleStmt editionStmt edition publicationStmt sourceDesc idno profileDesc langUsage language textClass classCode"/>
        <moduleRef key="core" include="p lb pb head label hi l lg list item rs choice sic corr unclear milestone note num title author bibl name date pubPlace publisher ref cit quote abbr cb"/>
        <moduleRef key="textstructure" include="TEI text front body div titlePage titlePart docTitle docAuthor docImprint docDate docEdition closer signed salute dateline epigraph byline"/>
        <moduleRef key="namesdates" include="persName surname forename"/>
        <moduleRef key="transcr" include="fw supplied space"/>
        <moduleRef key="figures" include="figure"/>
        <moduleRef key="linking" include="anchor"/>
        <moduleRef key="tei"/>

        <!-- ===================================================================
             ATTRIBUTE CLASSES — light trimming; keep behaviour permissive
             =================================================================== -->
        <classSpec type="atts" ident="att.cmc" mode="delete"/>
        <classSpec type="atts" ident="att.global.change" mode="delete"/>
        <classSpec type="atts" ident="att.global" mode="change">
          <attList>
            <attDef ident="xml:base" mode="delete"/>
            <attDef ident="xml:space" mode="delete"/>
          </attList>
        </classSpec>

        <!-- @rendition: a whitespace-separated list of pointer tokens declared in tagsDecl.
             Following tei_simplePrint, the value space is NOT closed here: new appearance
             tokens may be added by declaring them in tagsDecl. @rend / @style are removed. -->
        <classSpec type="atts" ident="att.global.rendition" mode="change">
          <attList>
            <attDef ident="rend" mode="delete"/>
            <attDef ident="style" mode="delete"/>
            <attDef ident="rendition" mode="change" usage="opt">
              <desc>One or more pointers to <gi>rendition</gi> elements in <gi>tagsDecl</gi>,
                recording the appearance of the source passage (e.g. <val>#aq</val>,
                <val>#et #aq</val>).</desc>
              <datatype minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="unbounded">
                <dataRef key="teidata.pointer"/>
              </datatype>
            </attDef>
          </attList>
        </classSpec>

        <!-- ===================================================================
             REUSABLE CONTENT — inline (phrase-level) model used across the
             transcription. Kept generous on purpose (WIP sources).
             =================================================================== -->
        <macroSpec ident="macro.simlerInline" mode="add">
          <desc>The phrase-level content shared by the transcription elements: text interspersed with
            highlighting, entity references, editorial interventions, note anchors and line/page/column
            breaks.</desc>
          <content>
            <alternate minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="unbounded">
              <textNode/>
              <elementRef key="hi"/>
              <elementRef key="rs"/>
              <elementRef key="choice"/>
              <elementRef key="unclear"/>
              <elementRef key="supplied"/>
              <elementRef key="num"/>
              <elementRef key="note"/>
              <elementRef key="anchor"/>
              <elementRef key="abbr"/>
              <elementRef key="fw"/>
              <elementRef key="head"/>
              <elementRef key="lb"/>
              <elementRef key="pb"/>
              <elementRef key="cb"/>
            </alternate>
          </content>
        </macroSpec>

        <!-- ===================================================================
             ROOT, HEADER
             =================================================================== -->
        <elementSpec ident="TEI" module="textstructure" mode="change">
          <desc>The root element of a Simler edition document: one <gi>teiHeader</gi> followed by one
            <gi>text</gi>. <att>type</att> is required.</desc>
          <content>
            <sequence>
              <elementRef key="teiHeader"/>
              <elementRef key="text"/>
            </sequence>
          </content>
          <attList>
            <attDef ident="type" mode="change" usage="req">
              <valList type="closed" mode="replace">
                <valItem ident="simler-framework"><desc>Simler edition document</desc></valItem>
              </valList>
            </attDef>
          </attList>
          <exemplum>
            <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
              <TEI type="simler-framework"><teiHeader><!-- ... --></teiHeader><text><!-- ... --></text></TEI>
            </egXML>
          </exemplum>
        </elementSpec>

        <elementSpec ident="teiHeader" module="header" mode="change">
          <model behaviour="metadata"/>
          <desc>Document metadata: a <gi>fileDesc</gi> and an optional (possibly empty)
            <gi>profileDesc</gi>.</desc>
          <content>
            <sequence>
              <elementRef key="fileDesc"/>
              <elementRef key="profileDesc" minOccurs="0"/>
            </sequence>
          </content>
        </elementSpec>

        <elementSpec ident="fileDesc" module="header" mode="change">
          <desc>The bibliographic description of the file.</desc>
          <content>
            <sequence>
              <elementRef key="titleStmt"/>
              <elementRef key="editionStmt" minOccurs="0"/>
              <elementRef key="publicationStmt"/>
              <elementRef key="sourceDesc"/>
            </sequence>
          </content>
        </elementSpec>

        <elementSpec ident="titleStmt" module="header" mode="change">
          <desc>One or more <gi>title</gi>s and an optional <gi>author</gi>.</desc>
          <content>
            <sequence>
              <elementRef key="title" minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="unbounded"/>
              <elementRef key="author" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="unbounded"/>
            </sequence>
          </content>
        </elementSpec>

        <elementSpec ident="title" module="core" mode="change">
          <desc>A title of the edited text.</desc>
          <content><macroRef key="macro.phraseSeq"/></content>
          <attList>
            <attDef ident="type" mode="change" usage="opt">
              <valList type="semi" mode="replace">
                <valItem ident="main"><desc>main title</desc></valItem>
                <valItem ident="sub"><desc>subtitle</desc></valItem>
              </valList>
            </attDef>
          </attList>
          <exemplum>
            <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
              <title type="main">TEIL 3 VON: Johann-Wilhelm Simlers teutscher Getichten die dritte
                […] Aussfertigung</title>
            </egXML>
          </exemplum>
        </elementSpec>

        <elementSpec ident="author" module="core" mode="change">
          <desc>The author of the edited text, normally a structured <gi>persName</gi>.</desc>
          <content>
            <alternate minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="unbounded">
              <textNode/><elementRef key="persName"/>
            </alternate>
          </content>
          <exemplum>
            <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
              <author><persName ref="http://d-nb.info/gnd/119151693"><surname>Simler</surname><forename>Johann
                Wilhelm</forename></persName></author>
            </egXML>
          </exemplum>
        </elementSpec>

        <elementSpec ident="persName" module="namesdates" mode="change">
          <desc>A personal name; <att>ref</att> links to an external authority record (GND).</desc>
          <content>
            <alternate minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="unbounded">
              <textNode/><elementRef key="surname"/><elementRef key="forename"/>
            </alternate>
          </content>
        </elementSpec>

        <elementSpec ident="editionStmt" module="header" mode="change">
          <content><elementRef key="edition"/></content>
        </elementSpec>
        <elementSpec ident="edition" module="header" mode="change">
          <content><macroRef key="macro.phraseSeq"/></content>
          <exemplum>
            <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
              <edition>Vollständige digitalisierte Ausgabe.</edition>
            </egXML>
          </exemplum>
        </elementSpec>

        <elementSpec ident="publicationStmt" module="header" mode="change">
          <desc>The publication statement: one or more paragraphs, or structured
            publisher/place/date.</desc>
          <content>
            <alternate minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="unbounded">
              <elementRef key="p"/>
              <elementRef key="publisher"/>
              <elementRef key="pubPlace"/>
              <elementRef key="date"/>
            </alternate>
          </content>
          <exemplum>
            <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
              <publicationStmt><p>unknown</p></publicationStmt>
            </egXML>
          </exemplum>
        </elementSpec>

        <elementSpec ident="sourceDesc" module="header" mode="change">
          <desc>Describes the digitised printed source.</desc>
          <content><elementRef key="bibl" minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="unbounded"/></content>
        </elementSpec>

        <elementSpec ident="bibl" module="core" mode="change">
          <desc>A loosely structured bibliographic reference holding the identifiers of the
            digitised source.</desc>
          <content>
            <alternate minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="unbounded">
              <textNode/><elementRef key="idno"/><elementRef key="title"/><elementRef key="author"/>
            </alternate>
          </content>
          <attList>
            <attDef ident="type" mode="change" usage="opt">
              <valList type="semi" mode="replace">
                <valItem ident="M"><desc>monograph</desc></valItem>
              </valList>
            </attDef>
          </attList>
          <exemplum>
            <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
              <bibl><idno type="URLIIIF">https://www.e-rara.ch/i3f/v20/4049159/manifest</idno></bibl>
            </egXML>
          </exemplum>
        </elementSpec>

        <elementSpec ident="idno" module="header" mode="change">
          <desc>An identifier or URI for the source.</desc>
          <content>
            <alternate minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="unbounded">
              <textNode/><elementRef key="idno"/>
            </alternate>
          </content>
          <attList>
            <attDef ident="type" mode="change" usage="opt">
              <valList type="semi" mode="replace">
                <valItem ident="URLIIIF"><desc>URL of the IIIF presentation manifest (e-rara)</desc></valItem>
                <valItem ident="URLImages"><desc>URL of the page images</desc></valItem>
                <valItem ident="URLCatalogue"><desc>URL of the library catalogue record</desc></valItem>
                <valItem ident="Transkribus"><desc>Transkribus document/collection identifier</desc></valItem>
                <valItem ident="shelfmark"><desc>library shelfmark of the printed copy</desc></valItem>
              </valList>
            </attDef>
          </attList>
        </elementSpec>

        <elementSpec ident="profileDesc" module="header" mode="change">
          <desc>Optional descriptive profile (language usage, classification). May be empty.</desc>
          <content>
            <alternate minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="unbounded">
              <elementRef key="langUsage"/><elementRef key="textClass"/>
            </alternate>
          </content>
        </elementSpec>

        <!-- ===================================================================
             TEXT STRUCTURE
             =================================================================== -->
        <elementSpec ident="text" module="textstructure" mode="change">
          <desc>The transcribed text: an optional <gi>front</gi> and a <gi>body</gi>. A front-matter
            volume (e.g. the title-page/dedication part of an edition) may carry <gi>front</gi>
            without a <gi>body</gi>.</desc>
          <content>
            <sequence>
              <elementRef key="front" minOccurs="0"/>
              <elementRef key="body" minOccurs="0"/>
            </sequence>
          </content>
        </elementSpec>

        <elementSpec ident="front" module="textstructure" mode="change">
          <desc>Front matter: title page(s) and prefatory divisions (dedication, frontispiece).</desc>
          <content>
            <alternate minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="unbounded">
              <elementRef key="titlePage"/><elementRef key="div"/><elementRef key="figure"/>
              <elementRef key="milestone"/><elementRef key="lb"/><elementRef key="pb"/>
            </alternate>
          </content>
        </elementSpec>

        <elementSpec ident="body" module="textstructure" mode="change">
          <desc>The body of the document, holding the page/line stream and the hierarchy of
            structural divisions.</desc>
          <content>
            <alternate minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="unbounded">
              <elementRef key="div"/><elementRef key="lg"/><elementRef key="head"/>
              <elementRef key="pb"/><elementRef key="lb"/><elementRef key="milestone"/>
              <elementRef key="fw"/>
            </alternate>
          </content>
        </elementSpec>

        <elementSpec ident="div" module="textstructure" mode="change">
          <model behaviour="block">
            <outputRendition>margin: 1.5em 0;</outputRendition>
          </model>
          <desc>A structural division — a book, a group of poems, or an individual poem. <att>type</att>
            classifies the division; <att>n</att> records its level/running number.</desc>
          <content>
            <alternate minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="unbounded">
              <textNode/>
              <elementRef key="div"/><elementRef key="head"/><elementRef key="lg"/>
              <elementRef key="p"/><elementRef key="list"/><elementRef key="label"/>
              <elementRef key="closer"/><elementRef key="figure"/><elementRef key="note"/>
              <elementRef key="fw"/><elementRef key="cb"/><elementRef key="anchor"/>
              <elementRef key="milestone"/><elementRef key="lb"/><elementRef key="pb"/>
              <elementRef key="hi"/><elementRef key="rs"/><elementRef key="choice"/>
              <elementRef key="unclear"/><elementRef key="supplied"/><elementRef key="num"/>
            </alternate>
          </content>
          <attList>
            <attDef ident="type" mode="change" usage="opt">
              <valList type="semi" mode="replace">
                <valItem ident="poem"><desc>an individual poem</desc></valItem>
                <valItem ident="dedication"><desc>a dedication</desc></valItem>
                <valItem ident="frontispiece"><desc>a frontispiece</desc></valItem>
              </valList>
            </attDef>
          </attList>
          <exemplum>
            <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
              <div n="3" type="poem">
                <head><hi rendition="#aq #c">III.</hi></head>
                <lb/>
                <lg type="poem"><!-- ... --></lg>
              </div>
            </egXML>
          </exemplum>
        </elementSpec>

        <!-- ===== title page ===== -->
        <elementSpec ident="titlePage" module="textstructure" mode="change">
          <model behaviour="block">
            <outputRendition>text-align: center; margin: 2em auto; padding-bottom: 1em; border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;</outputRendition>
          </model>
          <desc>A title page transcribed within <gi>front</gi>.</desc>
          <content>
            <alternate minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="unbounded">
              <elementRef key="docTitle"/><elementRef key="titlePart"/><elementRef key="docAuthor"/>
              <elementRef key="docImprint"/><elementRef key="docDate"/><elementRef key="docEdition"/>
              <elementRef key="figure"/><elementRef key="label"/><elementRef key="milestone"/>
              <elementRef key="lb"/><elementRef key="pb"/>
            </alternate>
          </content>
          <attList>
            <attDef ident="type" mode="change" usage="opt"/>
          </attList>
        </elementSpec>
        <elementSpec ident="docTitle" module="textstructure" mode="change">
          <content>
            <alternate minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="unbounded">
              <elementRef key="titlePart"/><elementRef key="lb"/>
            </alternate>
          </content>
        </elementSpec>
        <elementSpec ident="titlePart" module="textstructure" mode="change">
          <content>
            <alternate minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="unbounded">
              <textNode/><elementRef key="hi"/><elementRef key="lb"/><elementRef key="list"/>
            </alternate>
          </content>
          <attList>
            <attDef ident="type" mode="change" usage="opt">
              <valList type="semi" mode="replace">
                <valItem ident="main"/><valItem ident="desc"/>
              </valList>
            </attDef>
          </attList>
        </elementSpec>
        <elementSpec ident="docAuthor" module="textstructure" mode="change">
          <content><macroRef key="macro.simlerInline"/></content>
        </elementSpec>
        <elementSpec ident="docImprint" module="textstructure" mode="change">
          <content>
            <alternate minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="unbounded">
              <textNode/><elementRef key="hi"/><elementRef key="pubPlace"/>
              <elementRef key="publisher"/><elementRef key="docDate"/><elementRef key="lb"/>
            </alternate>
          </content>
        </elementSpec>
        <elementSpec ident="docDate" module="textstructure" mode="change">
          <content><macroRef key="macro.simlerInline"/></content>
        </elementSpec>
        <elementSpec ident="pubPlace" module="core" mode="change">
          <content><macroRef key="macro.simlerInline"/></content>
        </elementSpec>
        <elementSpec ident="publisher" module="core" mode="change">
          <content><macroRef key="macro.simlerInline"/></content>
        </elementSpec>

        <!-- ===================================================================
             VERSE
             =================================================================== -->
        <elementSpec ident="lg" module="core" mode="change">
          <model behaviour="block">
            <outputRendition>margin: 1em 0;</outputRendition>
          </model>
          <desc>A group of verse lines — in the Simler edition typically a poem
            (<att>type</att>=<val>poem</val>) or a sub-group/stanza.</desc>
          <content>
            <alternate minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="unbounded">
              <elementRef key="l"/><elementRef key="lg"/><elementRef key="head"/>
              <elementRef key="label"/><elementRef key="p"/><elementRef key="note"/>
              <elementRef key="cb"/><elementRef key="milestone"/><elementRef key="lb"/>
              <elementRef key="pb"/>
            </alternate>
          </content>
          <attList>
            <attDef ident="type" mode="change" usage="opt">
              <valList type="semi" mode="replace">
                <valItem ident="poem"><desc>a poem</desc></valItem>
                <valItem ident="poem-subgroup"><desc>a sub-group of a poem</desc></valItem>
                <valItem ident="stanza"><desc>a stanza</desc></valItem>
              </valList>
            </attDef>
            <attDef ident="n" mode="change" usage="opt"/>
          </attList>
          <exemplum>
            <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
              <lg type="poem">
                <l><hi rendition="#in">W</hi>Er schälk’ und spötter fleucht/ und Gottes wort be<lb break="no"/>trachtet/</l>
                <lb/>
                <l rendition="#et">der gru&#x364;net wie ein baum an einem wasserfluß/</l>
              </lg>
            </egXML>
          </exemplum>
        </elementSpec>

        <elementSpec ident="l" module="core" mode="change">
          <model behaviour="block">
            <outputRendition>margin: 0; line-height: 1.5;</outputRendition>
          </model>
          <desc>A single verse line. <att>rendition</att> records the indentation of the printed
            line; line/word breaks of the setting are encoded with <gi>lb</gi>.</desc>
          <content>
            <alternate minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="unbounded">
              <textNode/><elementRef key="hi"/><elementRef key="rs"/><elementRef key="choice"/>
              <elementRef key="unclear"/><elementRef key="supplied"/><elementRef key="num"/>
              <elementRef key="label"/><elementRef key="note"/><elementRef key="anchor"/>
              <elementRef key="space"/><elementRef key="lb"/><elementRef key="pb"/>
            </alternate>
          </content>
          <attList>
            <attDef ident="n" mode="change" usage="opt"/>
          </attList>
          <exemplum>
            <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
              <l rendition="#et">der wird <rs type="place" key="place_027">Sion</rs>sfeind’ auch straffen sonder fehl.</l>
            </egXML>
          </exemplum>
        </elementSpec>

        <!-- ===================================================================
             PHRASE-LEVEL TRANSCRIPTION
             =================================================================== -->
        <elementSpec ident="hi" module="core" mode="change">
          <!-- inline; the actual look (italic/bold/centring/…) comes from the
               @rendition pointer, resolved to .r-* CSS from <tagsDecl>. -->
          <model behaviour="inline"/>
          <desc>A typographically distinct span of the source. <att>rendition</att> is required on
            <gi>hi</gi> (it is optional elsewhere) and points to one or more <gi>rendition</gi>
            declarations in <gi>tagsDecl</gi>; tokens combine (e.g. <val>#aq #c</val>). <gi>hi</gi>
            may nest.</desc>
          <content><macroRef key="macro.simlerInline"/></content>
          <attList>
            <attDef ident="rendition" mode="change" usage="req"/>
          </attList>
          <exemplum>
            <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
              <head><hi rendition="#b #c">Aller<lb/> Psalmen Davids Haubt<lb break="no"/>begriff/</hi></head>
            </egXML>
          </exemplum>
        </elementSpec>

        <elementSpec ident="head" module="core" mode="change">
          <model behaviour="heading">
            <param name="level" value="count(ancestor::div)"/>
            <outputRendition>font-size: 1.2em; text-align: center; margin: 0.8em 0 0.4em;</outputRendition>
          </model>
          <desc>A heading of a <gi>div</gi>, <gi>lg</gi>, <gi>list</gi> or <gi>figure</gi>.</desc>
          <content>
            <alternate minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="unbounded">
              <textNode/><elementRef key="hi"/><elementRef key="label"/><elementRef key="num"/>
              <elementRef key="rs"/><elementRef key="choice"/><elementRef key="unclear"/>
              <elementRef key="supplied"/><elementRef key="note"/><elementRef key="fw"/>
              <elementRef key="anchor"/><elementRef key="lb"/><elementRef key="pb"/>
            </alternate>
          </content>
          <attList>
            <attDef ident="n" mode="change" usage="opt"/>
          </attList>
          <exemplum>
            <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
              <head>
                <label>[1.]</label>
                <lb/>
                <hi rendition="#b #c">[Das erst bu&#x364;ch der Psalmen.]</hi>
              </head>
            </egXML>
          </exemplum>
        </elementSpec>

        <elementSpec ident="label" module="core" mode="change">
          <model behaviour="inline">
            <outputRendition>font-variant: small-caps; color: #555;</outputRendition>
          </model>
          <desc>A label, typically the (often editorially supplied, bracketed) number of a heading or
            poem.</desc>
          <content><macroRef key="macro.simlerInline"/></content>
          <exemplum>
            <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"><label>[2.]</label></egXML>
          </exemplum>
        </elementSpec>

        <elementSpec ident="num" module="core" mode="change">
          <model behaviour="inline"/>
          <desc>A number (Roman or Arabic) marked as such in the source.</desc>
          <content><macroRef key="macro.simlerInline"/></content>
        </elementSpec>

        <elementSpec ident="p" module="core" mode="change">
          <model behaviour="paragraph"/>
          <desc>A prose paragraph (e.g. closing formulae of a book, captions, header notes).</desc>
          <content>
            <alternate minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="unbounded">
              <textNode/><elementRef key="hi"/><elementRef key="rs"/><elementRef key="choice"/>
              <elementRef key="unclear"/><elementRef key="supplied"/><elementRef key="num"/>
              <elementRef key="note"/><elementRef key="ref"/><elementRef key="lg"/>
              <elementRef key="anchor"/><elementRef key="fw"/><elementRef key="lb"/>
              <elementRef key="pb"/>
            </alternate>
          </content>
          <exemplum>
            <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
              <p><hi rendition="#smaller #c">Ende des ersten buchs der<lb/> Psalmen Davids.</hi></p>
            </egXML>
          </exemplum>
        </elementSpec>

        <!-- ===== entity reference ===== -->
        <elementSpec ident="rs" module="core" mode="change">
          <!-- Entity reference, colour-coded by @type. The per-type predicates
               compile to a JS if-chain in the spine and to data-type selectors
               in the CSS floor. -->
          <model predicate="@type='person'" behaviour="inline">
            <outputRendition>color: #8e44ad;</outputRendition>
          </model>
          <model predicate="@type='place'" behaviour="inline">
            <outputRendition>color: #2980b9;</outputRendition>
          </model>
          <model predicate="@type='org'" behaviour="inline">
            <outputRendition>color: #16a085;</outputRendition>
          </model>
          <model predicate="@type='institution'" behaviour="inline">
            <outputRendition>color: #16a085;</outputRendition>
          </model>
          <model predicate="@type='work'" behaviour="inline">
            <outputRendition>font-style: italic; color: #b9770e;</outputRendition>
          </model>
          <model predicate="@type='bibl'" behaviour="inline">
            <outputRendition>font-style: italic; color: #7f8c8d;</outputRendition>
          </model>
          <model behaviour="inline">
            <outputRendition>border-bottom: 1px dotted #aaa;</outputRendition>
          </model>
          <desc>A referencing string identifying a named entity. <att>type</att> classifies the
            entity; <att>key</att> is the typed identifier of the entry in the project registers
            (its prefix should match <att>type</att>).</desc>
          <content>
            <alternate minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="unbounded">
              <textNode/><elementRef key="hi"/><elementRef key="rs"/><elementRef key="choice"/>
              <elementRef key="unclear"/><elementRef key="supplied"/><elementRef key="note"/>
              <elementRef key="anchor"/><elementRef key="lb"/>
            </alternate>
          </content>
          <attList>
            <attDef ident="type" mode="change" usage="req">
              <valList type="semi" mode="replace">
                <valItem ident="person"><desc>person</desc></valItem>
                <valItem ident="place"><desc>place</desc></valItem>
                <valItem ident="org"><desc>organisation</desc></valItem>
                <valItem ident="institution"><desc>institution</desc></valItem>
                <valItem ident="work"><desc>literary work</desc></valItem>
                <valItem ident="bibl"><desc>bibliographic item</desc></valItem>
              </valList>
            </attDef>
            <attDef ident="key" mode="change" usage="req">
              <desc>The typed entity identifier, normally of the form
                <val>{type}_{id}</val> (e.g. <val>person_049</val>).</desc>
              <datatype><dataRef key="teidata.text"/></datatype>
            </attDef>
          </attList>
          <exemplum>
            <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
              <l>Der <rs type="person" key="person_049">David</rs> setzt auf Gott sein hoffnung und vertrauen/</l>
            </egXML>
          </exemplum>
        </elementSpec>

        <!-- ===== editorial interventions ===== -->
        <elementSpec ident="choice" module="core" mode="change">
          <model behaviour="alternate"/>
          <desc>Groups the source reading (<gi>sic</gi>) and its editorial correction
            (<gi>corr</gi>), in either order.</desc>
          <content>
            <alternate minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="unbounded">
              <elementRef key="sic"/><elementRef key="corr"/>
            </alternate>
          </content>
          <exemplum>
            <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
              <l>Wiewol ich krankner mir gedult hab <choice><sic>fu&#x364;rgenommen</sic><corr>fürgenommen</corr></choice>/</l>
            </egXML>
          </exemplum>
        </elementSpec>
        <elementSpec ident="sic" module="core" mode="change">
          <model behaviour="inline">
            <outputRendition>color: #c0392b;</outputRendition>
          </model>
          <desc>The reading actually present in the source, retained unchanged.</desc>
          <content><macroRef key="macro.simlerInline"/></content>
        </elementSpec>
        <elementSpec ident="corr" module="core" mode="change">
          <model behaviour="inline">
            <outputRendition>color: #1e8449;</outputRendition>
          </model>
          <desc>The editorial correction of an obvious printing error.</desc>
          <content><macroRef key="macro.simlerInline"/></content>
        </elementSpec>

        <elementSpec ident="supplied" module="transcr" mode="change">
          <model behaviour="inline">
            <outputRendition>color: #2980b9;</outputRendition>
          </model>
          <desc>Text supplied by the editors where the source is missing or illegible.
            <att>cert</att> may record the confidence of the supplement.</desc>
          <content><macroRef key="macro.simlerInline"/></content>
          <attList>
            <attDef ident="cert" mode="change" usage="opt">
              <valList type="semi" mode="replace">
                <valItem ident="high"/><valItem ident="low"/>
              </valList>
            </attDef>
          </attList>
        </elementSpec>

        <elementSpec ident="unclear" module="core" mode="change">
          <model behaviour="inline">
            <outputRendition>opacity: 0.65; font-style: italic;</outputRendition>
          </model>
          <desc>A passage that cannot be read with certainty; <att>reason</att> records why.</desc>
          <content><macroRef key="macro.simlerInline"/></content>
          <attList>
            <attDef ident="reason" mode="change" usage="opt">
              <valList type="semi" mode="replace">
                <valItem ident="uncleanPrint"><desc>illegible because of poor / unclean printing</desc></valItem>
                <valItem ident="covered"><desc>covered or obscured on the page</desc></valItem>
              </valList>
            </attDef>
          </attList>
          <exemplum>
            <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
              <l rendition="#et">die <unclear reason="uncleanPrint">kind</unclear> und […]</l>
            </egXML>
          </exemplum>
        </elementSpec>

        <elementSpec ident="abbr" module="core" mode="change">
          <desc>An abbreviation as it appears in the source.</desc>
          <content><macroRef key="macro.simlerInline"/></content>
        </elementSpec>

        <!-- ===================================================================
             NOTES, LISTS, FIGURES, REFERENCES
             =================================================================== -->
        <elementSpec ident="note" module="core" mode="change">
          <model behaviour="note">
            <outputRendition>font-size: 0.9em;</outputRendition>
          </model>
          <desc>An editorial note or comment. <att>type</att> classifies it; <att>targetEnd</att>
            (with a preceding <gi>anchor</gi> pair) delimits the commented range;
            <att>resp</att> records responsibility.</desc>
          <content>
            <alternate minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="unbounded">
              <textNode/><elementRef key="p"/><elementRef key="hi"/><elementRef key="rs"/>
              <elementRef key="lb"/>
            </alternate>
          </content>
          <attList>
            <attDef ident="type" mode="change" usage="opt">
              <valList type="semi" mode="replace">
                <valItem ident="annotation"><desc>an editorial annotation</desc></valItem>
              </valList>
            </attDef>
            <attDef ident="place" mode="change" usage="opt">
              <valList type="semi" mode="replace">
                <valItem ident="comment"><desc>an out-of-line editorial comment</desc></valItem>
                <valItem ident="right"/><valItem ident="bottom"/>
              </valList>
            </attDef>
          </attList>
        </elementSpec>

        <elementSpec ident="list" module="core" mode="change">
          <model behaviour="list"/>
          <desc>A list.</desc>
          <content>
            <alternate minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="unbounded">
              <elementRef key="head"/><elementRef key="item"/><elementRef key="lb"/>
              <elementRef key="pb"/>
            </alternate>
          </content>
        </elementSpec>
        <elementSpec ident="item" module="core" mode="change">
          <model behaviour="listItem"/>
          <content><macroRef key="macro.simlerInline"/></content>
        </elementSpec>

        <elementSpec ident="figure" module="figures" mode="change">
          <model behaviour="block">
            <outputRendition>margin: 1em auto; text-align: center; padding: 0.5em; border: 1px dashed #ccc;</outputRendition>
          </model>
          <desc>A figure (woodcut, frontispiece engraving, decorative element), optionally with a
            heading and descriptive paragraph.</desc>
          <content>
            <alternate minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="unbounded">
              <elementRef key="head"/><elementRef key="p"/><elementRef key="lb"/>
              <elementRef key="pb"/>
            </alternate>
          </content>
        </elementSpec>

        <elementSpec ident="ref" module="core" mode="change">
          <desc>A pointer/reference within the text.</desc>
          <content><macroRef key="macro.simlerInline"/></content>
        </elementSpec>

        <!-- ===================================================================
             CLOSERS (subscriptions, datelines, signatures)
             =================================================================== -->
        <elementSpec ident="closer" module="textstructure" mode="change">
          <desc>The closing matter of a division (e.g. a dedication): salutation, dateline and
            signature.</desc>
          <content>
            <alternate minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="unbounded">
              <textNode/><elementRef key="salute"/><elementRef key="dateline"/>
              <elementRef key="signed"/><elementRef key="rs"/><elementRef key="hi"/>
              <elementRef key="lb"/>
            </alternate>
          </content>
        </elementSpec>
        <elementSpec ident="salute" module="textstructure" mode="change">
          <content><macroRef key="macro.simlerInline"/></content>
        </elementSpec>
        <elementSpec ident="dateline" module="textstructure" mode="change">
          <content><macroRef key="macro.simlerInline"/></content>
        </elementSpec>
        <elementSpec ident="signed" module="textstructure" mode="change">
          <content><macroRef key="macro.simlerInline"/></content>
        </elementSpec>

        <!-- ===================================================================
             MILESTONE / BREAK / FORME-WORK ELEMENTS
             =================================================================== -->
        <elementSpec ident="milestone" module="core" mode="change">
          <!-- empty; the source rule appearance comes from @rendition (#hr). -->
          <model behaviour="block"/>
          <desc>An empty milestone marking a structural section boundary in the source.
            <att>unit</att> is required.</desc>
          <content><empty/></content>
          <attList>
            <attDef ident="unit" mode="change" usage="req">
              <valList type="semi" mode="replace">
                <valItem ident="section"><desc>a section boundary within the text</desc></valItem>
              </valList>
            </attDef>
          </attList>
          <exemplum>
            <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
              <milestone unit="section" rendition="#hr"/>
            </egXML>
          </exemplum>
        </elementSpec>

        <elementSpec ident="cb" module="core" mode="change">
          <desc>Marks the beginning or end of a column. <att>type</att>=<val>start</val>/<val>end</val>
            brackets a two-column passage.</desc>
          <content><empty/></content>
          <attList>
            <attDef ident="type" mode="change" usage="opt">
              <valList type="semi" mode="replace">
                <valItem ident="start"/><valItem ident="end"/>
              </valList>
            </attDef>
          </attList>
        </elementSpec>

        <elementSpec ident="anchor" module="linking" mode="change">
          <model behaviour="anchor"/>
          <desc>An anchor point delimiting a commented range (paired with a <gi>note</gi> via
            <att>targetEnd</att>). The range is keyed either by <att>xml:id</att> or by <att>n</att>
            on a start/end pair.</desc>
          <content><empty/></content>
          <attList>
            <attDef ident="type" mode="change" usage="opt">
              <valList type="semi" mode="replace">
                <valItem ident="commentRangeStart"/><valItem ident="commentRangeEnd"/>
              </valList>
            </attDef>
          </attList>
        </elementSpec>

        <elementSpec ident="space" module="transcr" mode="change">
          <desc>A significant blank space in the source.</desc>
          <content><empty/></content>
        </elementSpec>

        <elementSpec ident="fw" module="transcr" mode="change">
          <model behaviour="block">
            <outputRendition>font-size: 0.8em; color: #999; text-align: center; margin: 0.3em 0;</outputRendition>
          </model>
          <desc>Forme work — running material outside the text block (page numbers, signatures,
            catchwords, running headers). <att>type</att> classifies it, <att>place</att> locates
            it.</desc>
          <content>
            <alternate minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="unbounded">
              <textNode/><elementRef key="hi"/><elementRef key="num"/><elementRef key="choice"/>
              <elementRef key="unclear"/><elementRef key="supplied"/><elementRef key="note"/>
              <elementRef key="head"/><elementRef key="anchor"/><elementRef key="lb"/>
            </alternate>
          </content>
          <attList>
            <attDef ident="type" mode="change" usage="opt">
              <valList type="semi" mode="replace">
                <valItem ident="pageNum"><desc>a printed page number</desc></valItem>
                <valItem ident="catch"><desc>a catchword</desc></valItem>
                <valItem ident="sig"><desc>a printer's signature</desc></valItem>
                <valItem ident="header"><desc>a running header</desc></valItem>
              </valList>
            </attDef>
            <attDef ident="place" mode="change" usage="opt">
              <valList type="semi" mode="replace">
                <valItem ident="top"/><valItem ident="bottom"/>
              </valList>
            </attDef>
          </attList>
          <exemplum>
            <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
              <fw type="pageNum" place="top">194</fw>
            </egXML>
          </exemplum>
        </elementSpec>

        <!-- ===== pb: page beginning ===== -->
        <elementSpec ident="pb" module="core" mode="change">
          <!-- Boot's (2024) nested-model extension: a compound behaviour. With a
               @facs the page break renders as a thumbnail of the e-rara facsimile
               that links to the full-resolution scan — both IIIF image URLs are
               derived here from @facs, so the rendering logic stays in the ODD and
               the source keeps only the stable image identifier. Without @facs the
               same element falls back to a plain page-break rule. -->
          <model predicate="@facs" behaviour="compound">
            <modelSequence>
              <model behaviour="link">
                <param name="uri" value="concat(@facs, '/full/full/0/default.jpg')"/>
                <outputRendition>display: inline-block; margin: 0.6em 0;</outputRendition>
              </model>
              <model behaviour="graphic">
                <param name="url" value="concat(@facs, '/full/pct:25/0/default.jpg')"/>
                <outputRendition>max-width: 120px; border: 1px solid #ccc;</outputRendition>
              </model>
            </modelSequence>
          </model>
          <model behaviour="block">
            <outputRendition>display: block; border-top: 1px solid #ddd; margin: 1.4em 0; height: 0;</outputRendition>
          </model>
          <desc>Marks the beginning of a new printed page. <att>n</att> gives the printed page number
            (bracketed when editorially supplied); <att>facs</att> links to the facsimile.</desc>
          <content><empty/></content>
          <attList>
            <attDef ident="n" mode="change" usage="opt"/>
            <attDef ident="facs" mode="change" usage="opt">
              <desc>The IIIF image identifier URL of the page on e-rara (e.g.
                <val>https://www.e-rara.ch/i3f/v20/4049203</val>); the <gi>pb</gi> model builds the
                thumbnail and full-image links from it. Optional: absent for pages identified only by
                a printer's signature (e.g. <val>[A ii r]</val>) that have no separate facsimile.</desc>
              <datatype><dataRef key="teidata.pointer"/></datatype>
            </attDef>
          </attList>
          <exemplum>
            <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
              <pb n="194" facs="https://www.e-rara.ch/i3f/v20/4049203"/>
            </egXML>
          </exemplum>
        </elementSpec>

        <!-- ===== lb: line break (DTABf semantics) ===== -->
        <elementSpec ident="lb" module="core" mode="change">
          <desc>Marks the <emph>end</emph> of a printed line (Zeilenschluss), following the DTA base
            format convention (<ref target="https://www.deutschestextarchiv.de/doku/basisformat/lbAllg.html"
            >lbAllg</ref>). Placement rules:
            <list>
              <item><gi>lb</gi> is never implicit: every line end is marked explicitly, including the
                end of the first line of a block.</item>
              <item>when a line end coincides with the end of one or more elements, the <gi>lb</gi> is
                placed <emph>after the outermost closing tag</emph>, as a following sibling of that
                element — <emph>not</emph> as the last child inside it. In particular the line end of
                the last verse line of a poem follows the closing <gi>lg</gi> (and, where the
                <gi>lg</gi> is the last child of its <gi>div</gi>, the closing <gi>div</gi>), never
                the last <gi>l</gi>.</item>
              <item>only <gi>pb</gi>, <gi>cb</gi> and <gi>space</gi> stand without a following
                <gi>lb</gi>; and no <gi>lb</gi> is set immediately before
                <gi>front</gi>/<gi>body</gi>/<gi>back</gi>/<gi>titlePage</gi> closes.</item>
              <item>for a word hyphenated across the line, the visible hyphen is kept in the
                transcription and <att>break</att>=<val>no</val> is set on the <gi>lb</gi> at that
                line end.</item>
            </list>
            The Schematron constraint <ident>lb-line-end-placement</ident> checks that <gi>lb</gi> is
            not left as the last child of a line-bearing element.</desc>
          <content><empty/></content>
          <attList>
            <attDef ident="break" mode="change" usage="opt">
              <valList type="closed" mode="replace">
                <valItem ident="no"><desc>the line break falls inside a word (hyphenation): the
                  following line continues the broken word</desc></valItem>
                <valItem ident="yes"><desc>the line break coincides with a word boundary (the
                  default)</desc></valItem>
              </valList>
            </attDef>
          </attList>
          <exemplum>
            <p>The line end of the last verse line follows the <emph>outermost</emph> closing element
              — here after <gi>div</gi>, as a sibling of it — not inside <gi>lg</gi> after the last
              <gi>l</gi>:</p>
            <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
              <div type="poem">
                <lg type="poem">
                  <l>Die gwaltigen umsonst sich wider Christum lehnen:</l>
                  <lb/>
                  <l rendition="#et">dann Gottes rahtschluß muß fortgehen immerzu/</l>
                </lg>
              </div>
              <lb/>
            </egXML>
          </exemplum>
          <exemplum>
            <p>Counter-example — <emph>incorrect</emph>: the final <gi>lb</gi> must not be the last
              child of <gi>lg</gi>:</p>
            <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
              <lg type="poem">
                <l>dann Gottes rahtschluß muß fortgehen immerzu/</l>
                <lb/>
              </lg>
            </egXML>
          </exemplum>
          <exemplum>
            <p>Hyphenation: the hyphen is retained and <att>break</att>=<val>no</val> marks the
              continuation:</p>
            <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
              <l>und Gottes wort be<lb break="no"/>trachtet/</l>
            </egXML>
          </exemplum>
          <constraintSpec ident="lb-line-end-placement" scheme="schematron">
            <desc>Enforces the DTABf rule that a line break marks a line END placed after the
              outermost closing element: an <gi>lb</gi> may not be left as the last (significant)
              child of a line-bearing element such as <gi>lg</gi>, <gi>l</gi> or <gi>div</gi> — it
              should be moved to follow that element's closing tag.</desc>
            <constraint>
              <sch:rule xmlns:sch="http://purl.oclc.org/dsdl/schematron"
                context="tei:lb[not(following-sibling::*) and not(following-sibling::text()[normalize-space()])]">
                <sch:report role="warning"
                  test="parent::tei:l or parent::tei:lg or parent::tei:div or parent::tei:head
                      or parent::tei:p or parent::tei:list or parent::tei:item or parent::tei:hi
                      or parent::tei:closer or parent::tei:salute or parent::tei:signed
                      or parent::tei:dateline or parent::tei:titlePart or parent::tei:figure
                      or parent::tei:fw or parent::tei:body or parent::tei:front">
                  [S-LB] A line break (lb) marks a line END and must follow the outermost closing
                  element; here it is the last child of &lt;<sch:value-of select="local-name(parent::*)"/>&gt;.
                  Move the lb to immediately after the closing &lt;/<sch:value-of select="local-name(parent::*)"/>&gt; tag.
                </sch:report>
              </sch:rule>
            </constraint>
          </constraintSpec>
        </elementSpec>

      </schemaSpec>
    </body>
  </text>
</TEI>
